29/06/2005
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Members of EUFOR, NATO and the Republika Srpska (RS) police raided a number of facilities Wednesday (29 June) including two hotels and a private house owned by businessman Slavko Roguljic in the Banja Luka area. 
Roguljic, who is on the black lists of the EU and the United States, is suspected of helping UN tribunal indictee Radovan Karadzic elude capture. 
According to a statement from EUFOR, Wednesday's operation is aimed at finding evidence about the whereabouts of indictees and smashing their support network. 
(RTRS, PBS BiH - 29/06/05)
